.TH simple_shell 1 "December 2023" "Version 1.0" "simple_shell Manual"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple shell program

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBsimple_shell\fP program is a basic shell that allows users to interact with the system by entering commands.

.PP
When the shell is launched, it presents a command prompt (\fI$:\fP) and awaits user input. Users can enter commands along with optional arguments.

.PP
The shell then searches for the entered command in the system's PATH directories, and if found, it executes the command.

.SH OPTIONS
None

.SH EXAMPLES
To run a command in the shell, simply type the command and press Enter. For example:

.PP
.B $: ls

.PP
This will list the contents of the current directory.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR execve(2), \fIgetenv\fP(3), \fIgetline\fP(3), \fIstrtok\fP(3), \fIwaitpid\fP(2)

